HOSTNAME(5) - Local hostname configuration file
	- The /etc/hostname file configures the name of the local system.
	

MACHINE-ID(5) - Local machine ID configuration file
	- The /etc/machine-id file contains the unique machine ID of the local system that is set during installation or boot.
	
	
OS-RELEASE(5) - Operating system identification
	- The /etc/os-release and /usr/lib/os-release files contain operating system identification data.
	
	


HOSTNAME(1) - output or change current hostname
	options:
		-i: Display  the  network  address(es) of the host name.
		q

HOSTNAMECTL(1) - hostnamectl may be used to query and change the system hostname and related settings.

UUID(1) - The UUID library is used to generate unique identifiers for objects that may be accessible the local system.
	options:
		-o: write to file instead of stdout
		-F: format

UUIDGEN(1) - create a new UUID value

DBUS-UUIDGEN(1) - The dbus-uuidgen command generates or reads a universally unique ID.

UNAME(1) - print system information

LSB_RELEASE(1) - The lsb_release command provides certain LSB (Linux Standard Base) and distribution-specific information.

